  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package embeds a W-CON-03 consistency weakness: one validation result carries an evidenceTimestamp that is strictly later than the UnitOfAssurance signatureTimestamp, simulating a race-condition artifact in which evidence appears to have been generated after the package was formally signed.",
